@@eThe Scorched Wastes@@N

In older records this region appears as the @@yMeridian Intake March@@N:
a managed corridor of toll pavilions, cistern regulators, and charter
stations. Modern travelers see only dunes, venom pits, raiders, and
undead functionaries, because the corridor's institutions were not
merely abandoned -- they were @@rthermally and metaphysically
overprinted@@N.

The decisive event was the failed @@rNinth Meridian Rite@@N, an attempt
to fuse solar measurement and underworld descent authority into one
governing ritual. When the linked systems desynchronized, heat surged
through dry channels meant for water release. The result was a
sustained @@rburn wave@@N: dune glassing, structural collapse, undead
administrative persistence, and recurring eclipse mirage phenomena.

Three factions now contest the ruins. The @@yCharter Remnants@@N are
descendants of intake clerks and ration auditors -- some living
survivalists, others undead functionaries still demanding documents
and issuing citations before attacking when proper paperwork is not
produced. The @@rDune Host Reavers@@N are post-collapse logistics
predators who inherited route knowledge from ruined intake records,
hoarding water containers and legal tablets equally. The @@dSynod
Eclipse Cells@@N regard the Wastes as holy proof that failed synthesis
can be corrected, recut inscriptions, stage mock tribunals, and
conduct witness-burning rites.

Below them all, the ecology has responded. Scorpion broods nest in
collapsed embalming halls. @@eFaultline entities@@N -- heat echoes,
salt-lung shades, pressure phantoms -- manifest near dry governor
mechanisms, distorting sound and direction.

The Wastes share a common origin with the @@ySaltglass Reach@@N to the
east. The same thermal pulse that created this burn scar propagated
through the dry Iseth channel at attenuated intensity, fusing the
Reach's sand into glass. The Wastes received the full force; the
Reach received the echo.

Every room shows a former purpose and a post-catastrophe reuse.
Verdict halls are inhabited by revenants. Toll stones have been
recut as curses. Ration seals are worn by raiders. @@yLaw persists
after legitimacy dies.@@N @@rWater memory outlives water presence.@@N
Administrative tools become ritual weapons under scarcity.
